        "action": "Lower the maximum temperature allowed when transporting livestock after Brexit",
        "additional_details": "Current EU guidance: \r\nhttps://www.gov.uk/guidance/farm-animal-welfare-during-transportation#eu-regulation-on-the-welfare-of-animals-in-transport",
        "background": "EU rules require the ability to keep the temperature under 35\u00b0C in the animal compartment, when transporting livestock on journeys over eight hours. \r\n\r\n35\u00b0C is inhumane and does not cover shorter journeys. There is also no guarantee of protection for livestock after Brexit.",
